        <iri>
          <value>https://w3id.org/italia/real-estate/onto/StateProperty/BeneImmobileDelloStato</value>
          <annotations>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://w3id.org/italia/real-estate/onto/StateProperty/BeneImmobileDelloStato</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Bene immobile dello Stato</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>it</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://w3id.org/italia/real-estate/onto/StateProperty/BeneImmobileDelloStato</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>State Real Estate Asset</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://w3id.org/italia/real-estate/onto/StateProperty/BeneImmobileDelloStato</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Bene immobile (812 c.c.), appartenente allo Stato, assoggettato ai regimi giuridici previsti dal Codice Civile e dalle leggi speciali vigenti.
I beni immobili dello Stato, in gestione all’Agenzia del Demanio, si classificano in:
• Beni patrimoniali immobili indisponibili: beni immobili appartenenti allo Stato non rientranti nella categoria dei beni demaniali (art. 826 ss.c.c.).
• Beni immobili patrimoniali disponibili: tutti i beni immobili di proprietà dello Stato diversi dai beni demaniali e patrimoniali indisponibili (art. 828 c.c.).
Per quanto concerne i beni demaniali (art. 822 c.c.), la gestione dell’Agenzia del Demanio è riferita unicamente a quelli d'interesse storico / artistico non già in gestione al Ministero per i Beni Culturali.</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>it</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://w3id.org/italia/real-estate/onto/StateProperty/BeneImmobileDelloStato</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Real estate (Article 812 of the Italian Civil Code) belonging to the State, subject to the legal regimes established by the Civil Code and applicable special laws.
State-owned real estate, managed by the State Property Agency, is classified as follows:
• Unavailable immovable assets: real estate belonging to the State that does not fall within the category of state-owned property (Article 826 et seq. of the Italian Civil Code).
• Available immovable assets: all real estate owned by the State other than state-owned property and unavailable patrimonial property (Article 828 of the Italian Civil Code).
With regard to state-owned property (Article 822 of the Italian Civil Code), the management of the State Property Agency refers solely to those of historical/artistic interest not already managed by the Ministry of Cultural Heritage.</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
          </annotations>
        </iri>
        <iri>
          <value>https://w3id.org/italia/real-estate/onto/StateProperty/CategoriaBeneImmobile</value>
          <annotations>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://w3id.org/italia/real-estate/onto/StateProperty/CategoriaBeneImmobile</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Categoria di bene immobile dello Stato</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>it</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://w3id.org/italia/real-estate/onto/StateProperty/CategoriaBeneImmobile</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>State Real Estate Asset Category</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://w3id.org/italia/real-estate/onto/StateProperty/CategoriaBeneImmobile</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Tipologia di beni pubblici gestiti dall’Agenzia del Demanio:
- Beni Patrimoniali
- Demanio Artistico-Storico non in gestione al Ministero per i beni culturali
- Beni non di proprietà dello stato su cui lo Stato vanta diritti reali.</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>it</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://w3id.org/italia/real-estate/onto/StateProperty/CategoriaBeneImmobile</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Types of public assets managed by the State Property Agency:
- Heritage Assets
- Artistic-Historical State Property not managed by the Ministry of Cultural Heritage
- Non-state-owned assets over which the State holds real rights.</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
          </annotations>
        </iri>
